Our vision is to transform how the world uses information to enrich life.  Join an inclusive team passionate about one thing: using their expertise in the relentless pursuit of innovation for customers and partners. The solutions we build help make everything from virtual reality experiences to breakthroughs in neural networks possible. We do it all while committing to integrity, sustainability, and giving back to our communities. Because doing so can fuel the very innovation we are pursuing. 
 
The Corporate Vice President, Strategy and Communications is a key leadership role reporting directly to the EVP, Chief Business Officer and will be responsible for overseeing and providing thought leadership for the following functions: Corporate Strategy, Corporate Development, and the Global Communications & Marketing organizations. This position will identify and address strategic questions facing the company, engage key executives to identify gaps in Micronâ€™s capabilities, translate gaps into opportunities, and execute against Micronâ€™s long-range strategic plan. This role will act as an advisor to the CBO & CEO on critical changes in the competitive landscape and external business environment. Oversee the creation of quarterly/annual briefings and present complex business plans to executive leadership and the board of directors. Communicate grounded recommendations to senior leaders and their broader organizations, influencing upwards and laterally to drive organizational change and alignment. Lead corporate wide efforts to drive the development of new emerging ecosystems, standards or industry wide initiatives that will lead to the buildup of new business focus areas. This position can be upgraded to a Senior Vice-President role for the right candidate. 
 
Other Responsibilities include:
 Represent Micron in strategic external communications with customers, press, analysts, etc. 
Represent, advocate and partner with other organizations for the needs of the Strategy and Communications group 
Mentor, develop and empower senior leaders, ensuring successors for key roles within business unit 
Oversee critical talent acquisition and retention to ensure long-term organizational success 
Provide cross functional leadership and influence by working effectively with senior leaders throughout the organization to drive company strategy and initiatives 
 
Requirements: 
Seasoned professional with strategy orientation, who has successfully led multiple business or operation organizations in large, globally diverse, publicly traded companies 
Deep understanding of competitive dynamics and strategies of key industry players, technical and other differentiated capabilities required to win in the marketplace 
Strong executive presence and demonstrated success leading top performing teams; ability to motivate, drive and inspire change 
15 years of experience in the semiconductor industry 
Masterâ€™s degree in Engineering/Science; MBA a plus 
 
